  "title": "The Prism Bastion — Ledger Ramparts of Light",
  "narration": "Descending from the Echo Cascade, you arrive at the Prism Bastion: a fortress carved from refracted daylight and nightlight fused into polygonal walls. Each rampart is a ledger stone split into seven faces, each face representing a faction’s trust levels. The air glitters with micro-spectra; breathing them tastes like cold rosemary, minted citrus, and charged quartz. When you walk, your footprints leave lattices of gold that fade only after being audited.\n\nThe Bastion is managed by the Ray-Binder gremlin faction. Their capes are arrays of prisms strung together with copper wire. Dev gremlins maintain light-routing code, traders hedge luminosity futures, whales run wake channels through the moat of photons, hackers rewrite spectral firewalls, shillers broadcast brand new rays, validators record each shine, miners chisel photon ore, and memes scatter lens-flare jokes on every walkway. They greet you with a double GM — sunrise and sunset overlapped — and escort you to the ramparts to begin the next seven-round gauntlet.\n\nWithin the Bastion, consensus rituals become strategic war games: you must position spectrum cannons, calibrate defense runes, maintain AFK turrets, and revive teammates whose reflections shatter under pressure. Soft-power equipment here includes radiant shields, prism helms, and rumor-splitting blades that convert gossip into guidance. Spectrum doors appear as portcullises of light, each requiring synchronized golden-ratio pulses to unlock. Hidden difficulty tiers lurk within refraction mazes; if you misalign even slightly, the fortress reconfigures around you.\n\nSeven rounds lay out like command orders. Each provides phi-d20 checks, opportunities to gain XP, Coins, Focus, Flags, Items, Decks, and threshold rewards that escalate with precision. Telemetry glyphs record each action, later transmuted into training modules for future arrivals. Ray-Binders whisper jokes while handing you tactical ledgers — their humor is gremlin-grade but their expectations are severe. The Bastion expects you to shine and document every glimmer.",
